  "prompt": "Can someone screenshot a snap after I block them?",
  "response": "When you block someone on Snapchat:\n1. They cannot see your Snapchat story\n2. They cannot send you new snaps or messages\n3. Their previous conversations with you will disappear\n\nHowever, if they had already screenshot a snap before you blocked them, that screenshot would still exist. Once blocked, they cannot take new screenshots of your content. If you're concerned about a specific snap being screenshotted, blocking them after the fact won't remove any existing screenshots they may have taken.",
